SIMPLE: topper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topper
<hw>Top"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One that
tops, in any sense of the verb;</def> <specif>specif.:</specif>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A cover of a top layer or part.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One that excels, surpasses, or
is extraordinary of its kind.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>Any device for cutting off tops; <as>as, a turnip
<ex>topper</ex></as>.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>One who tops steel
ingots.</def> <sd>(e)</sd> <def>A three-square float (file) used by comb
makers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A top hat.</def> <mark>[Slang or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tobacco left in the bottom of a pipe bowl; -- so
called from its being often taken out and placed on top of the newly
filled bowl. Also, a cigar stump.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toppiece</ent>⟦br⟧
